cs.ET, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.CV, cs.LG

The paper deals with the problem of layout fracturing for e-beam lithography, which is a subfield of electronic design automation (EDA) and semiconductor manufacturing. Therefore, cs.ET (EDA and VLSI) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes algorithms for optimizing the fracturing process, which involves computational geometry and optimization techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with image processing and pattern recognition, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and machine learning, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
